Betadine

A person enters the pharmacy , asking for some Betadine for their friend who came off his skateboard and this is the stuff that their mum told them to get.

Questions Case

Person presenting or another. Description: Age, sex 		A young teen
What is the problem:
Decription of symptoms.

The patient had been skate-boarding and has bailed out of a gnarly rail grind to avoid a collision with a mother with a pram.
He/She wasnt wearing protective gloves and consequently has grazed each of their palms and knuckles form the asphalt in the skate park. The skin is broken and the wounds are oozing blood.

If asked: bailed out means jumped off a gnarly rail grind is when you travel along a rail on your skateboard The site of the graze is quite painful. The site is quite grubby
